[[File:Nightsister_Force_Crystal.jpg|thumb|A Nightsister Force Crystal]]
{{Quote|I have noticed that many of these witches wear elaborate headdresses. I have been told that within these hats, they contain a special stone. I believe that this stone is the source of their "magic".|Xarot Korlin|<ref name="SWG:XK">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=static|Xarot Korlin|Dathomir}}</ref>}}
A '''Nightsister Force Crystal''' was a crystal native to [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]] that was capable of enhancing the [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsisters]]' [[The Force/Legends|Force]] abilities. Nightsisters wore it as part of their elaborate [[Clothing/Legends|headdresses]]. [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Imperial Inquisitor]] [[Xarot Korlin]], who had been studying the [[Homeworld/Legends|indigenous]] Nightsisters' ways of using the Force, sent an agent to [[Death/Legends|kill]] one of them to obtain one of these crystals for his studies. The agent noticed that the crystal was very cold to the touch. The agent also felt uneasy having it on their person.<ref name="SWG:XK" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Nightsister Force Crystal appeared in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:NFC">{{SWGcite|exp=AED|type=item|Nightsister Force Crystal}}</ref> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> This crystal was an item available through a quest for Imperial Inquisitor Xarot Korlin. By killing a Nightsister, collecting the crystal and then deleting the quest, players were able to retain the crystal for themselves.<ref name="SWG:XK" /> The crystals had no Force-enhancing effect, but instead could be used as a decoration for players' houses.<ref name="SWG:NFC" />

